meta:
  origin:
    producer: Pershing et al.
    title: Whale populations (Pershing et al. 2010)
    description: |-
      Estimates of whale populations pre-whaling and in 2001, published by Pershing et al. (2010) and originally sourced from Christensen (2006).

      The dates of pre-whaling differ depending on the whale species and oceanic region, ranging from as far back as 1530 for Right whales. The most common pre-whaling date in the original source was in the late 19th and early 20th century. All pre-whaling dates have been coded as 1890 for consistency, but it should be noted that this date varies by species. The latest date — 2001 — is consistent across species.

      All estimates are of the global total.
    citation_full: 'Pershing, A. J., Christensen, L. B., Record, N. R., Sherwood, G. D., and Stetson, P. B. (2010). The impact of whaling on the ocean carbon cycle: why bigger was better. PloS One, 5(8), e12444.'
    url_main: https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0012444
    date_accessed: '2019-08-28'
    date_published: '2010'
